    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Here's what <a href=\"http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/clopts-139448.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Oracle's documentation</a> has to say:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>By default the heap dump is created in\n  a file called java_<em>pid</em>.hprof in the\n  working directory of the VM, as in the\n  example above. You can specify an\n  alternative file name or directory\n  with the <code>-XX:HeapDumpPath=</code> option. For\n  example <code>-XX:HeapDumpPath=/disk2/dumps</code>\n  will cause the heap dump to be\n  generated in the <code>/disk2/dumps</code>\n  directory.</p>\n</blockquote>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3709402,
      "reputation" : 569,
      "user_id" : 3087118,
      "user_type" : "unregistered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/96e98946f135542ebf6638efff49224b?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Swaminathan Krishnamoorthi",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3087118/swaminathan-krishnamoorthi"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 56,
    "last_activity_date" : 1386684800,
    "last_edit_date" : 1386684800,
    "creation_date" : 1386683648,
    "answer_id" : 20496376,
    "question_id" : 542979,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can view this dump from the UNIX console.</p>\n\n<p>The path for the heap dump will be provided as a variable right after where you have placed the mentioned variable.</p>\n\n<p>E.g.:</p>\n\n<pre><code>-XX:+HeapDumpOnOutOfMemoryError -XX:HeapDumpPath=${DOMAIN_HOME}/logs/mps\"\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>You can view the dump from the console on the mentioned path.</p>\n"
  }, {
